Define the trait interfaces that all embedding and reranker backends implement,
plus a registry that produces the correct backend from configuration.

## Embedder Trait Design
```rust
/// Category of embedding model (for benchmark classification)
#[derive(Debug, Clone, Copy, PartialEq, Eq, Serialize, Deserialize)]
pub enum ModelCategory {
    StaticEmbedder,       // Model2Vec, static-retrieval-mrl
    TransformerEmbedder,  // MiniLM, BGE, Nomic, Gemma (ONNX inference)
}

/// Sync trait: all methods block. Daemon backend wraps async UDS in block_on().
pub trait Embedder: Send + Sync {
    /// Embed a batch of texts, returning normalized vectors
    fn embed_batch(&self, texts: &[&str]) -> Result<Vec<Vec<f32>>>;
    /// Native embedding dimensions
    fn dimensions(&self) -> usize;
    /// Human-readable model identifier
    fn model_name(&self) -> &str;
    /// Model category for benchmark classification
    fn category(&self) -> ModelCategory;
    /// Whether this model supports Matryoshka truncation
    fn supports_mrl(&self) -> bool { false }
    /// Truncate embeddings to target_dim (only if supports_mrl)
    /// IMPORTANT: Must re-normalize after truncation!
    fn truncate(&self, embeddings: &[Vec<f32>], target_dim: usize) -> Result<Vec<Vec<f32>>> {
        if target_dim > self.dimensions() {
            anyhow::bail!("target_dim {} > native dims {}", target_dim, self.dimensions());
        }
        Ok(embeddings.iter().map(|e| {
            let truncated: Vec<f32> = e[..target_dim].to_vec();
            let norm = truncated.iter().map(|x| x * x).sum::<f32>().sqrt();
            truncated.iter().map(|x| x / norm).collect()
        }).collect())
    }
}
```

## Reranker Trait Design
```rust
pub trait Reranker: Send + Sync {
    /// Score (query, document) pairs, returning relevance scores
    fn rerank(&self, query: &str, documents: &[&str]) -> Result<Vec<f32>>;
    /// Human-readable model identifier
    fn model_name(&self) -> &str;
    /// Maximum input token length
    fn max_length(&self) -> usize;
}
```

## Model Registry
```rust
pub enum EmbedderBackend {
    StaticMrl,       // static-retrieval-mrl-en-v1 → ModelCategory::StaticEmbedder
    Model2Vec,       // potion-retrieval-32M → ModelCategory::StaticEmbedder
    FastEmbed(FastEmbedModel), // MiniLM, BGE, Nomic, Gemma → ModelCategory::TransformerEmbedder
    Daemon,          // Connects to warm daemon via UDS (any category)
}

pub enum RerankerBackend {
    FlashRank,       // ~4MB nano model
    MxbaiXSmall,     // 0.1B cross-encoder
    None,            // Skip reranking
}

pub struct ModelRegistry {
    cache_dir: PathBuf,  // ~/.cache/xf/models/
}

impl ModelRegistry {
    /// Create an embedder from config
    pub fn embedder(&self, config: &EmbedderConfig) -> Result<Box<dyn Embedder>>;

    /// Create a reranker from config (None if disabled)
    pub fn reranker(&self, config: &RerankerConfig) -> Result<Option<Box<dyn Reranker>>>;

    /// Convenience: create reranker by name string (used by CLI/pipeline)
    /// Parses name into RerankerConfig internally
    pub fn reranker_by_name(&self, name: &str) -> Result<Box<dyn Reranker>> {
        let config = RerankerConfig::from_name(name)?;
        self.reranker(&config)?
            .ok_or_else(|| anyhow::anyhow!("Unknown reranker: {name}"))
    }

    /// Convenience: create embedder by name string
    pub fn embedder_by_name(&self, name: &str) -> Result<Box<dyn Embedder>> {
        let config = EmbedderConfig::from_name(name)?;
        self.embedder(&config)
    }

    /// List all known model names with their categories
    pub fn list_models(&self) -> Vec<ModelInfo>;
}

#[derive(Debug, Serialize)]
pub struct ModelInfo {
    pub name: String,
    pub category: ModelCategory,
    pub backend: String,
    pub supports_mrl: bool,
    pub native_dims: usize,
    pub size_mb: Option<f64>,  // None if not downloaded
    pub downloaded: bool,
}
```

## Model Download and Caching
- Models stored in ~/.cache/xf/models/ (respect XDG_CACHE_HOME)
- ONNX files downloaded on first use with progress bar
- Checksum verification after download
- xf models list shows installed models and sizes
- xf models download <name> pre-downloads for offline use

