### Behavior Matrix
| Flag | Progress | Warnings | Errors | Details | Debug/Trace |
|------|----------|----------|--------|---------|-------------|
| (none) | ✓ | ✓ | ✓ | ✗ | ✗ |
| -q | ✗ | ✗ | ✓ | ✗ | ✗ |
| -v | ✓ | ✓ | ✓ | ✓ | ✗ |
| -vv | ✓ | ✓ | ✓ | ✓ | ✓ |

### Quiet Mode Effects
- Progress bars: Hidden
- Spinners: Hidden
- Info messages: Hidden
- Warnings: Hidden (only errors shown)
- Success messages: Hidden
- Only final output (JSON/CSV/text results) printed
- Tracing: ERROR level only

### Verbose Mode Effects
- Error panels show --details section
- Index command shows per-file progress
- Search shows query analysis breakdown
- Stats shows additional metrics
- Doctor shows check details
- Tracing: INFO level

### Debug Mode Effects
- All verbose output
- Query parse tree displayed
- Index timing breakdown per phase
- Memory usage stats
- Stack traces on errors
- Tracing: DEBUG level (full trace output)

### JSON/CSV Output Behavior
Verbosity flags DO NOT affect structured output formats:
- JSON output: Always machine-readable, no progress/debug text mixed in
- CSV output: Always clean rows, no progress/debug text mixed in
- Progress/debug goes to stderr when format is JSON/CSV

```rust
impl Output {
    /// Print to appropriate stream based on format
    pub fn print_progress(&self, text: &str) {
        if self.is_quiet() {
            return;
        }

        // For structured formats, progress goes to stderr
        if matches!(self.format, OutputFormat::Json | OutputFormat::Csv) {
            eprintln!("{}", text);
        } else {
            self.print(text);
        }
    }
}
